review_blob: Its beautiful. Deep aroma with cherry and chocolate. Taste could be thicker. Alcohol is well hidden which makes it really drinkable.

Tap@lhus Stockholm, Helsinki. Aroma is composty and not as fresh as you would expect from a citra pale ale. the taste continues with same tone of muddy disappointment. Palate, color and aftertaste are stable.
Looks like a beer I have made myself. the color is brown and dull. Taste starts with a fresh kick which is supported by sweet malts and banana. Not my favorite weizen but my wife loves it.
beer_name: Frankenthaler Durlacher Hof Weissbier Dunkel (Dark Wheat Beer)

review_blob: From a plastic cup in Seoul. The smell is mild but the taste suprises with its fruitu hoppiness and medium bitterness. Great beer with pulled pork sandwich.
